snippet.textDisplay:
People bashing Coke Studio for not exceeding their expectations; if you think singing is so easy then try it for yourself. Looks or no looks, these two are singing beautifully. Learn to encourage new talent. That's why new talent is always struggling because even before they are out there they are being torn down. And as far as nepotism goes, Daniyal Zafar clearly shares his skills with his brother and maybe that's because of genetics and maybe the fact that his brother must have mentored him. Every genre requires different kind of singing style. This song is unique to Strings' genre and that's what they are known for, and these have the appropriate style for the genre. It's a good song. Everyone has a unique taste in music, but if it doesn't appease your taste that doesn't mean it's a bad song. Respect the talent and others taste/opinion instead of bashing everyone in the most horrible language. It's only giving a bad message about your own upbringing and bad image of our country to fellow listeners from other countries. 
P.S. Also, I'm pretty sure they have a visible chemistry because they are already good friends.
